# SahelCast 🌱
**AI-powered planting advisory system for smallholder farmers in Ouaddaï, Chad**

Built by Adji Zamtato | Kansas State University | Agricultural Economics

## What It Does
SahelCast fuses free U.S. satellite data (CHIRPS, MODIS, SMAP) to tell 
farmers in Ouaddaï, Chad exactly when to plant their millet and sorghum 
crops — delivered as a simple RED/YELLOW/GREEN advisory via SMS.

## Validation Results
| Season | Date | Score | Status |
|--------|------|-------|--------|
| Dry Season | March 2026 | 0 🔴 | DO NOT PLANT ✅ |
| Early Season | June 2023 | 1 🟡 | WAIT ✅ |
| Peak Season | August 2023 | 2 🟢 | PLANT NOW ✅ |

## Data Sources (All Free)
- CHIRPS Daily Rainfall (USGS/UCSB)
- MODIS NDVI MOD13Q1 (NASA)
- SMAP Soil Moisture SPL3SMP_E (NASA)

## Scripts
1. `01_CHIRPS_Seasonal_Rainfall.js` — Seasonal rainfall mapping
2. `02_Baseline_Anomaly_Detection.js` — 20-year baseline comparison
3. `03_MODIS_NDVI_Stress.js` — Vegetation stress detection
4. `04_SMAP_Soil_Moisture.js` — Soil moisture planting trigger
5. `05_Planting_Advisory_Combined.js` — Final GREEN/YELLOW/RED output

## Built With
- Google Earth Engine (JavaScript API)
- CHIRPS, MODIS, SMAP satellite datasets
- Kansas State University computing resources
